(47, 'test1writingpara1', 231210, '<p style="color: rgb(40, 40, 40);background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">You should spend about<span> </span><b><b>40</b></b><span> </span>minutes on this task.</p><p style="color: rgb(40, 40, 40);background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">Write about the following topic:</p><p class="Indent1" style="color: rgb(40, 40, 40);background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><em><strong><b>Nowadays the way many people interact with each other has changed because of technology.</b></strong></em></p><p class="Indent1" style="color: rgb(40, 40, 40);background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><em><strong><b>In what ways has technology affected the types of relationships people make? Has this become a positive or negative development?</b></strong></em></p><p style="color: rgb(40, 40, 40);background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">Give reasons for your answer and include any relevant examples from your own knowledge or experience.</p><p style="color: rgb(40, 40, 40);background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">You should write at least<span> </span><b><b>250</b></b><span> </span>words.</p><!--EndFragment--><p><br/></p><p><br/></p>', 0, 0, 'writing', '', '', '2018-09-27 22:52:41'),
(48, 'test1writingpara2', 124555, '<p style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><font color="#c77f7f">You should spend about <b><b>40</b></b> minutes on this task.</font></p><p style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><font color="#c77f7f">Write about the following topic:</font></p><p class="Indent1" style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><em><strong><b><font color="#c77f7f">Nowadays the way many people interact with each other has changed because of technology.</font></b></strong></em></p><p class="Indent1" style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><em><strong><b><font color="#c77f7f">In what ways has technology affected the types of relationships people make? Has this become a positive or negative development?</font></b></strong></em></p><p style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><font color="#c77f7f">Give reasons for your answer and include any relevant examples from your own knowledge or experience.</font></p><p style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><font color="#c77f7f">You should write at least <b><b>250</b></b> words.</font></p><!--EndFragment--><p><br/></p><p><br/></p>', 0, 0, 'writing', '', '', '2018-09-27 22:53:48'),
(49, 'Test5para1', 726952, '<h1><strong><b>READING PASSAGE 1</b></strong></h1><div><strong><b><em>You should spend about 20 minutes on <strong><b>Questions 1-13</b></strong>, which are based </em></b></strong></div><div><strong><b><em>on Reading Passage 1 below.</em></b></strong></div><div><strong><b><!--EndFragment--><i><br/></i><br/></b></strong><img src="https://ieltsonlinetests.com/sites/default/files/2017-12/Ancient%20Chinese%20Chariots.jpg" style="height: 256px;width: 392px;"/><strong><b><br/></b></strong></div><p><strong style="color: rgb(40, 40, 40);text-align: justify;background-color: rgb(214, 228, 218);"><b><br/></b></strong></p><p><strong><b>A </b></strong><span>The Shang Dynasty or Yin Dynasty, according to traditional historiography, ruled in the Yellow River valley in the second millennium. Archaeological work at the Ruins of Yin (near modern-day Anyang), which has been identified as the last Shang capital, uncovered eleven major Yin royal tombs and the foundations of palaces and ritual sites, containing weapons of war and remains from both animal and human sacrifices.</span></p><p><span><!--StartFragment--><strong style="color: rgb(40, 40, 40);text-align: justify;background-color: rgb(214, 228, 218);"><b>B</b></strong><span> The Tomb of Fu Hao is an archaeological site at Yinxu, the ruins of the ancient Shang Dynasty capital Yin, within the modem city of Anyang in Henan Province, China. Discovered in 1976，it was identified as the final resting place of the queen and military general Fu Hao. The artifacts unearthed within the grave included jade objects, bone objects, bronze objects etc. These grave goods are confirmed by the oracle texts, which constitute almost all of the first hand written record we possess of the Shang Dynasty. Below the corpse was a small pit holding the remains of six sacrificial dogs and along the edge lay the skeletons of human slaves, evidence of human sacrifice.</span></span></p><p><span><strong><b>C </b></strong><span>The Terracotta Army was discovered on 29 March 1974 to the east of Xian in Shaanxi. The terracotta soldiers were accidentally discovered when a group of local farmers was digging a well during a drought around 1.6 km (1 mile) east of the Qin Emperors tomb around at Mount Li (Lishan), a region riddled with underground springs and watercourses. Experts currently place the entire number of soldiers at 8,000 — with 130 chariots (130 cm long), 530 horses and 150 cavalry horses helping to ward of any dangers in the afterlife. In contrast, the burial of Tutank Hamun yielded six complete but dismantled chariots of unparalleled richness and sophistication. Each was designed for two people (90 cm long) and had its axle sawn through to enable it to be brought along the narrow corridor into the tomb.</span></span></p><p><span><strong style="color: rgb(103, 106, 108);background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><b><b>D </b></b></strong><span style="color: rgb(103, 106, 108);background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">The Terracotta Army was discovered on 29 March 1974 to the east of Xian in Shaanxi. The terracotta soldiers were accidentally discovered when a group of local farmers was digging a well during a drought around 1.6 km (1 mile) east of the Qin Emperors tomb around at Mount Li (Lishan), a region riddled with underground springs and watercourses. Experts currently place the entire number of soldiers at 8,000 — with 130 chariots (130 cm long), 530 horses and 150 cavalry horses helping to ward of any dangers in the afterlife. In contrast, the burial of Tutank Hamun yielded six complete but dismantled chariots of unparalleled richness and sophistication. Each was designed for two people (90 cm long) and had its axle sawn through to enable it to be brought along the narrow corridor into the tomb.</span></span></p><p><span><span style="color: rgb(103, 106, 108);background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><strong style="color: rgb(103, 106, 108);background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><b><b><b>E <