ipline of biology from a purely lab-based science into an information science as well. The implications behind this change, for both science and medicine, are staggering.</p>', '<p>The passage suggests that bioinformaticians are attempting to develop algorithms to</p>', 4, 'Test5_Sec2_v19', '<p>The correct answer is (C).  The author discusses that algorithms are being developed to “predict protein structure and/or function.” None of the other answer choices are listed as areas in which algorithms are being developed.</p>', 1001),
(1728, 0, 919829, 'Verbal', '<p>Which sentence best indicates that Mississippi was not already a thriving colony when this investment scheme was occurring.</p>', '<p>As long as there has been a stock market, it has played a significant role in national and global economies., While the American “Black Tuesday” crash of 1929 is the best known, and often cited as the impetus for the Great Depression, this cataclysmic event is far from the first collapse with global implications., While examples of stock can be found in Rome in the second century BC, the incarnation that is foundational to the contemporary global markets emerged in eighteenth century Europe. , The emergence of the stock market represents one of the nascent stages of the transition from the land-based economy to one based on monetary wealth., As European powers engaged in colonizing the Americas, the creation of joint-stock companies became a way for investors to pool resources and share profits., As this practice expanded and exploration in the colonies became profitable, so came the practice of speculation., This presumption that favorable growth was the inevitable result of investment is the flawed practice that has resulted in collapses, including that of the French Market in 1720., When financier John Law proliferated rumors of the untold wealth of this emerging market, investors quickly purchased stock in the ailing Mississippi Company., When this wealth failed to materialize, it was ruinous for numerous venture capitalists whose wealth soon evaporated., These kinds of “bubbles” in the stock market will undoubtedly remain one of the enduring features of this economic structure.</p>', 6, 'Test5_Sec2_v20', '<p>Credited Selection: When financier John Law proliferated rumors of the untold wealth of this emerging market, investors quickly purchased stock in the ailing Mississippi Company.The eighth sentence is the correct one.  The use of the term “emerging market” suggests that Mississippi was underdeveloped and thus capable of producing potentially huge financial returns in the future.</p>', 1001),
